SonarQube in Docker
************************************
>Step 1:Install a docker 
  command :vim docker-setup.sh

  Here,the above command create and open the file,and add the docker installation script then install the docker 
   check 'docker --version' 

>Step 1:Create one sonarqube image

  command:docker pull sonarqube:lts

>Step 2:Create one sonarqube continer with the image name

  command:docker run -d \
--name sonarqube \
-p 9000:9000 \
sonarqube:lts

>Step 3:Host confriguration of port number

  command:firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=9000/tcp
          firewall-cmd --reload

>Step 4:open the browser with ip address and port number
  example :192.168.106.134


>Step 6:Set you username and password

            
